formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1)Details provided in Annexure-A i.e. Statement of calculation of receivables from the real estate project, booking of garages and parkings and valuation of unsold inventory and other details are based on management representation provided to us.
2)As per explanation received from management , we have been informed that unsecured loan taken from lendors is not used for construction purpose but was used for marketing purpose. Hence interest paid on unsecured loans has not been considered in development cost incurred and paid.
3)As per verification of books of accounts , we found that in few cases collection/booking amount received from buyers has been deposited in current account of promotor instead RERA account . Whereas as per RERA regulation once project is registered with RERA authority then 70% of the balance receivables of ongoing projects will have to be deposited in designated ( RERA ) account.
